abbr: Application Binary Interface

The ABI «lies» between the → Linux/kernel/process#user-kernel-space[user space] and the kernel space.

Contrast with API (Application Programming Interface).

There are four different levels of ABI stability:
  • stable (`→ Linux/kernel/source/Documentation/ABI/stable`)
  • testing (`→ Linux/kernel/source/Documentation/ABI/testing`)
  • obsolete (`→ Linux/kernel/source/Documentation/ABI/obsolete`)
  • removed (`→ Linux/kernel/source/Documentation/ABI/removed`)


sa:

 `scripts/get_abi.pl`

  → Linux/kernel/source/Documentation/ABI
